The ethical issue here is not whether or not to allow "citizens [to] throw their money away", but rather whether others should knowingly take it. Just because someone is willing to part with money due to ignorance or addiction doesn't mean that it's ethical for another to accept it with awareness of the the one's ignorance or addiction.That's the real ethical issue with gambling, but curiously that never gets discussed. Perhaps the people doing the collecting are also stifling that awkward and inconvenient discussion?
