Posted: Fri Mar 27, 2009 1:58 pm
In my mind this is the music industry vs. digital downloads, blockbuster vs. digital downloads, thing playing itself out again and will do so everywhere a "dinosaur", the old way of doing something, comes up against the latest craze. Yes there is a group of people who are morally and ethically opposed to gambling, but every facet of our society faces the same criticisms whether the participants are the same or not. Let's be honest, we fight about everything; breast feeding in public, breast feeding at all, breast feeding is porn or not, to the rabid vegans who want us all to eat grass whether by choice or force. The addiction argument is virtually groundless because there are people who are addicted to buying shoes but no one proposes getting rid of shoes or handbags for that matter (sorry ladies). Honestly there are people who live in poverty solely because they are giving all their money to their church, yes church, and no one is complaining there either.Why aren't Vegas and other gambling establishments allowed to go online. Are they even in support of it or would it kill the hotels and shows. This is a lot like Tesla vs. GM. GM had the EV1 or whatever that car was years ago and they forced the people with the cars to give them back so they could destroy them because its hard to say oh this is hard to build when the proof is out there on the highway. Tesla is here today with a car that is everything (sans cheap) that we say we want and they're begging for money. Meanwhile we're propping up the old way of doing things, read GM, with billions in loans even though they seem to be years behind Tesla to market.You would think online gambling would be the panacea for the people saying I don't want gambling in my town because it brings crime and poor people who've lost it all wandering aimlessly or not into traffic. Fine, let the people stay home and do their satan's work, where they do all the rest of satan's work: in the freaking bed room. I don't buy the argument that the digital form is more evil than the actual thing. Horse Racing is legal in the US. Gambling on horse races is legal in the US. Slots, poker and craps are all legal somewhere in the US. Thus, the US doesn't really have a problem with these things.I suspect the real barriers to online gambling are the established players doing everything they can to protect their old school domination refusing to ignore the writing on the wall. One thing you can always count on politicians the world over to fight for is the established player especially when the opponent is progress.
